status.description: The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are not closed can be reopened.

comments.comment:
I think:

the ensemble is created successfully

is the most important information.

Paolo Antinori added lot of commits to hide this "problem" in proper places. Generally this "error" happens during "shutdown" phase of fabric (when components are deactivated and services are unregistered because container is being reprovisioned. In a while everything will activate/register again and will continue working without problems, but threads started from (now) inactive components are no longer necessary but are not forcibly stopped).
But I'll do my best to backport everything I find that's related to ENTESB-5206.

There's:

Could not find network address for preferred '10.8.180.238' when the addresses were: host-172-16-117-200.openstacklocal/172.16.117.200

in the above logs - please verify the env.

I suggest changing the priority. Most (all?) of Paolo Antinori's fixes were backported to 6.2.1 and the remaining "client is not started" exceptions are only temporary - ZK groups will retry operations after owning SCR components are reactivated.
Definitely not a blocker.
Verified with 187. As Grzegorz said, all errors can't be solved without a bigger refactoring
